    <stitle>7.3 Liter Diesel Engine Diagnostics (1991) - DIAGNOSTIC ANALYSIS - DIAGNOSTIC ANALYSIS PROCEDURES FOR -
        ...HIGH COOLANT TEMPERATURE OR LOSS
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="0">
        <title>...HIGH COOLANT TEMPERATURE OR LOSS</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Verify Problem:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Determine operating conditions when overheating occurs.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Refer to guideline temperature data in the "Performance Data Guidelines" located in the
                    rear of Section 5.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Check the following items:</para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>Radiator cap (pressure cap).</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>External leaks (pressurize system).</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Coolant solution (glycol contamination).</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Vee belts and tension (adjustments).</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Dash gauge and sender accuracy/calibration.</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Thermostat operation (stuck or near closed).</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Radiator cleanliness (in side and out).</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Shutter operation (if equipped).</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Air flow blockage (winter front, etc.).</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Verify Operation:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Operator's habits - running improper range.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Vehicle specifications - verify the guideline data is correct for the vehicle and job.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Accessory equipment - Is the equipment approved and installed correctly?</para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Engine Maintenance:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Clean, no oil leaks, no external coolant leaks.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Belt adjustments correct (use Krikit gauge).</para>
                <para>Refer to the following Operator's Manual for belt adjustment specifications:</para>
                <para>
                    <emph type="underscr">Engine Manual No.</emph>
                </para>
                <para>7.3 Liter 1 171 606 R
                    <emph type="bold">*</emph>
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect Cooling System:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Coolant must be clean and properly inhibited for the season.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Radiator cap operative. Use pressure test kit (ZTSE-2326). Check restriction at water
                    pump inlet. Should not exceed 40 in. H2O without pressure cap and engine at high idle.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Hoses - correct type and properly clamped.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Radiator clean and unobstructed by bent fins, pinched tubes, etc.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Radiator correct. Check repair history or use of "stop leaks". Check specifications of
                    radiator for vehicle.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Fan - proper specification for vehicle, proper fit in shroud. Properly installed.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Shutter control (if equipped) operative and correct set.</para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect Engine:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Water pump condition.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Thermostat and seal - proper specifications and operating correctly.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Static and dynamic timing.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Oil cooler - proper flow of both oil and water.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Engine power correct.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Coolant aeration from combustion gas leakage.</para>
                <para>* - Manual specified with latest revision</para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
